1
00:00:28,356 --> 00:00:33,277
The Passengers

2
00:01:23,424 --> 00:01:26,701
I've come to pick up a 4th grade student,
Marc Letessier.

3
00:01:27,269 --> 00:01:28,190
Your name?

4
00:01:28,310 --> 00:01:29,260
Moineau.

5
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:40,944
Too bad Madame Letessier
could not come.

6
00:01:41,582 --> 00:01:42,833
Moineau.

7
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:44,892
Excuse me?

8
00:01:45,354 --> 00:01:47,022
She is Madame Moineau now.

9
00:01:47,142 --> 00:01:48,494
Oh, forgive me.
I forgot.

10
00:01:49,411 --> 00:01:54,124
I find her decision to take Marc
out of school regrettable.

11
00:01:54,415 --> 00:01:56,099
It will disturb him needlessly.

12
00:01:56,361 --> 00:01:58,561
Couldn't it wait until summer?

13
00:01:59,226 --> 00:02:01,104
It's not for me to decide.

14
00:02:02,297 --> 00:02:04,769
I hope Marc was not
put in this school...

15
00:02:04,889 --> 00:02:07,794
only because we teach in French.

16
00:02:08,694 --> 00:02:11,239
Do you know if your wife
plans to put Marc...

17
00:02:11,359 --> 00:02:13,207
in a religious institution in Paris?

18
00:02:13,557 --> 00:02:16,257
He will go to a regular school.

19
00:02:17,657 --> 00:02:18,478
Very well.

20
00:02:22,588 --> 00:02:26,337
Tell Marc Letessier his step-father
is waiting in my office.

21
00:02:34,469 --> 00:02:37,330
Has Madame Moineau
quit her job at Air France?

22
00:02:37,331 --> 00:02:40,042
No, she was transfered to Paris.

23
00:02:47,178 --> 00:02:48,177
Come in.

24
00:02:50,872 --> 00:02:51,788
Hello, Marc.

25
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,522
Hello, Madam director.

26
00:02:55,411 --> 00:02:56,357
Hello.

27
00:02:57,112 --> 00:02:58,371
Hello, Alex.

28
00:03:09,781 --> 00:03:11,300
Put your seatbelt on.

29
00:03:11,899 --> 00:03:13,453
We're being followed.

30
00:03:14,263 --> 00:03:15,124
Come on!

31
00:03:16,734 --> 00:03:18,519
I think you lost him
at the turn.

32
00:03:18,757 --> 00:03:19,723
You'll see.

33
00:03:20,678 --> 00:03:23,682
The last time I saw you
we were on familiar terms.

34
00:03:24,007 --> 00:03:25,381
I've forgotten.

35
00:03:26,107 --> 00:03:28,007
Here he is again.

36
00:03:29,634 --> 00:03:31,016
Put your seatbelt on.

37
00:03:31,484 --> 00:03:33,661
He was parked
in front of the school.

38
00:03:33,781 --> 00:03:36,123
I saw him follow us
from there.

39
00:03:36,919 --> 00:03:38,694
Sit up
and put your seatbelt on.

40
00:03:39,777 --> 00:03:41,407
Maybe he's a spy.

41
00:03:42,063 --> 00:03:43,107
Who?

42
00:03:43,635 --> 00:03:45,507
The guy who's following us.

43
00:03:48,865 --> 00:03:50,373
GPU...
Have you heard?

44
00:03:50,374 --> 00:03:52,691
First of all,
it's not GPU...

45
00:03:52,762 --> 00:03:54,391
it's called KGB now.

46
00:03:54,721 --> 00:03:56,412
And why
would they follow us?

47
00:03:56,806 --> 00:04:00,630
Simple!
They mistook our car for another.

48
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,963
A bit amateurish
those spies of yours.

49
00:04:03,593 --> 00:04:06,007
Or maybe
they're industrial spies.

50
00:04:06,008 --> 00:04:09,356
Or a private detective paid by...

51
00:04:09,695 --> 00:04:14,163
the school director
to make sure I donate at churches.

52
00:04:14,972 --> 00:04:16,990
You don't believe in God?

53
00:04:19,118 --> 00:04:20,071
Why do you ask?

54
00:04:20,314 --> 00:04:21,753
Just asking.

55
00:04:25,841 --> 00:04:28,127
Here's the entrance
to the highway.

56
00:04:44,773 --> 00:04:45,892
What are you doing?

57
00:04:46,664 --> 00:04:48,016
Just like I thought.

58
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:49,121
What?

59
00:04:49,122 --> 00:04:50,953
They're taking the highway too.

60
00:04:50,954 --> 00:04:52,523
Of course!

61
00:04:53,107 --> 00:04:55,804
No law forbids spies
to use the highway.

62
00:04:59,078 --> 00:05:00,617
Will you put
that seatbelt on?

63
00:05:00,846 --> 00:05:03,839
Really, old man,
1897 km of nagging...

64
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:05,647
Won't be fun.

65
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,292
1897 km?

66
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,929
I did the math
from the map.

67
00:05:11,138 --> 00:05:12,415
We'll be there after tomorrow.

68
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:13,587
After tomorrow?

69
00:05:14,393 --> 00:05:16,007
Why didn't we fly with mom?

70
00:05:16,719 --> 00:05:18,923
Your mom wanted us
to bring her car.

71
00:05:19,043 --> 00:05:21,066
Your mom loves her car.

72
00:05:22,049 --> 00:05:25,912
Since I love your mom,
I promised to bring her car.

73
00:05:26,383 --> 00:05:28,046
She doesn't want us
to drive at night,...

74
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:29,893
so it will take 3 days.

75
00:05:30,551 --> 00:05:33,777
If you want the whole story,
your mom figured...

76
00:05:33,778 --> 00:05:35,959
it would do us good
to spend some time together.

77
00:05:36,197 --> 00:05:38,615
So we get to know each other.

78
00:05:38,616 --> 00:05:41,253
She didn't ask my advice
when she married you.

79
00:05:42,045 --> 00:05:43,898
I don't see why
she'd feel guilty now.

80
00:05:44,117 --> 00:05:45,790
Don't flatter yourself, kid.

81
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:47,760
It's not about guilt.

82
00:05:48,444 --> 00:05:50,304
If you don't want us
to be friends...

83
00:05:50,305 --> 00:05:52,563
your mom will get over it,
and I will too.

84
00:05:53,107 --> 00:05:55,107
It's no tragedy.

85
00:05:59,698 --> 00:06:02,329
So far I like your type.

86
00:06:03,324 --> 00:06:04,916
And what type is that?

87
00:06:04,917 --> 00:06:07,882
The no nonsense type.

88
00:06:41,907 --> 00:06:42,510
What will it be?

89
00:06:42,729 --> 00:06:44,118
Black coffee for me.

90
00:06:44,459 --> 00:06:46,066
And for the young man?

91
00:06:46,401 --> 00:06:47,382
What would you like?

92
00:06:47,474 --> 00:06:48,683
Same thing as you.

93
00:06:48,803 --> 00:06:49,971
You're not having black coffee.

94
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:52,521
Cappuccino
with lots of milk.

95
00:06:52,826 --> 00:06:55,732
Not a cappuccino!
Makes me sick.

96
00:06:56,104 --> 00:06:57,678
Black coffee at your age?

97
00:06:57,798 --> 00:07:00,101
My age, my age...
Like you know anything.

98
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:02,682
You don't have to be rude.

99
00:07:04,122 --> 00:07:07,168
Give him what he likes.
A black coffee.

100
00:07:10,528 --> 00:07:12,328
I didn't want to offend you,
but...

101
00:07:12,944 --> 00:07:15,746
I don't like to be treated like this,
that's all.

102
00:07:16,847 --> 00:07:18,363
I am not offended.

103
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:20,638
Would you like some sugar?

104
00:07:20,639 --> 00:07:21,739
No.

105
00:07:38,227 --> 00:07:43,924
Could you ask for some milk?
It tastes bad.

106
00:07:48,450 --> 00:07:50,346
A drop of milk, please.

107
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,762
Full tank, please.

108
00:08:01,262 --> 00:08:03,076
Don't say anything.
I'll try to guess.

109
00:08:03,276 --> 00:08:04,507
Milan?

110
00:08:05,048 --> 00:08:06,440
Enno, you try.

111
00:08:07,873 --> 00:08:08,526
- Rome?
- No.

112
00:08:08,595 --> 00:08:10,420
- What then?
- Paris.

113
00:08:10,607 --> 00:08:12,743
Two in a row.
Impossible!

114
00:08:14,107 --> 00:08:16,537
Paris!
They all go to Paris!

115
00:08:26,976 --> 00:08:28,853
That's our route?

116
00:08:28,854 --> 00:08:29,943
Yes.

117
00:08:32,032 --> 00:08:33,751
Where do we stay tonight?

118
00:08:33,752 --> 00:08:35,278
Look, it's written there.

119
00:08:35,797 --> 00:08:38,170
Orvieto.
Holiday Inn Hotel.

120
00:08:38,357 --> 00:08:39,971
It's all booked and all that?

121
00:08:40,337 --> 00:08:41,313
And all that.

122
00:08:41,314 --> 00:08:42,907
Couldn't you plan more?

123
00:08:43,308 --> 00:08:45,237
Believe me,
after driving all day...

124
00:08:45,272 --> 00:08:47,891
I'd rather not have to search
for a hotel room.

125
00:08:48,455 --> 00:08:51,196
Like I said:
mom is marrying an organizer.

126
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,066
That's a big change for her.

127
00:08:54,265 --> 00:08:55,159
Really?

128
00:08:55,194 --> 00:08:55,914
Oh yeah.

129
00:08:56,664 --> 00:08:58,453
By the way,
what do you do for work?

130
00:08:58,471 --> 00:08:59,835
Accountant?

131
00:08:59,907 --> 00:09:00,836
Engineer.

132
00:09:02,673 --> 00:09:04,459
What about your career plans?

133
00:09:08,107 --> 00:09:09,278
Hey.

134
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:12,199
I asked you a question.

135
00:09:14,969 --> 00:09:16,043
Writer.

136
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:17,725
Writer?

137
00:09:18,297 --> 00:09:19,243
Yes.

138
00:09:21,409 --> 00:09:23,097
Why didn't you want
to tell me?

139
00:09:23,962 --> 00:09:25,216
I was afraid you'd laugh.

140
00:09:25,508 --> 00:09:27,635
Laugh?
I think it's great.

141
00:09:28,382 --> 00:09:29,009
Really?

142
00:09:29,338 --> 00:09:30,797
I'll still have to pay your bills...

143
00:09:30,824 --> 00:09:31,738
when you're 40.

144
00:09:31,938 --> 00:09:32,784
Not necessarily.

145
00:09:33,025 --> 00:09:34,778
Some writers
make a lot of money.

146
00:09:35,227 --> 00:09:36,200
Yes, some do.

147
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:41,443
Did you see that?

148
00:09:42,449 --> 00:09:42,997
Yes, I did.

149
00:09:43,087 --> 00:09:44,490
How do you explain that?

150
00:09:45,744 --> 00:09:46,618
Simple.

151
00:09:47,691 --> 00:09:51,013
Instead of stopping
at the cafe with us...

152
00:09:51,107 --> 00:09:52,126
he had his coffee break here.

153
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:54,285
And since his speed
is equal to ours...

154
00:09:54,307 --> 00:09:55,908
it was inevitable
we'd meet again.

155
00:09:57,066 --> 00:09:57,829
Are you convinced?

156
00:09:58,158 --> 00:10:00,910
You'll say the same thing
if we see him after dinner.

157
00:10:23,598 --> 00:10:26,868
If everyone did like you,
life would be easier.

158
00:10:27,856 --> 00:10:29,902
They all come
between 7 and 8.

159
00:10:30,107 --> 00:10:32,417
It's always a big mess.

160
00:10:32,807 --> 00:10:34,541
Now is the perfect time.

161
00:10:35,219 --> 00:10:37,035
- Going far?
- Paris.

162
00:10:37,396 --> 00:10:39,852
I'll take a burger with salad.

163
00:10:40,824 --> 00:10:43,172
Some people are lucky.

164
00:10:43,607 --> 00:10:46,038
All my life I've dreamt
of going to Paris.

165
00:10:46,513 --> 00:10:48,701
You'll go, some day.

166
00:10:49,408 --> 00:10:50,919
How much do you think
I make here?

167
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:52,853
With or without tips?

168
00:10:53,295 --> 00:10:54,320
With tips.

169
00:10:54,665 --> 00:10:56,666
Not much.

170
00:10:57,357 --> 00:10:59,957
So how could I go to Paris?

171
00:11:07,301 --> 00:11:09,519
- Are you expecting someone?
- No!

172
00:11:10,107 --> 00:11:13,631
- How about...
- Yes, burger and salad.

173
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:35,070
I am done.

174
00:11:35,532 --> 00:11:38,341
What?
You can't leave all that.

175
00:11:39,050 --> 00:11:39,957
You said you were hungry.

176
00:11:40,307 --> 00:11:42,427
I don't eat very much.

177
00:11:42,707 --> 00:11:44,932
You'll get used to it -
I sleep a lot instead.

178
00:11:46,389 --> 00:11:47,735
I sleep like crazy.

179
00:11:48,057 --> 00:11:52,042
If I'm not woken up,
I sleep 13-15 hours.

180
00:11:52,607 --> 00:11:53,678
It always scares mom.

181
00:11:53,907 --> 00:11:56,103
She always thinks
I'm dead or sick.

182
00:11:56,303 --> 00:11:58,736
Have some cheese though.

183
00:11:59,157 --> 00:12:00,507
And what if I don't?

184
00:12:00,907 --> 00:12:02,607
I'll leave you here to hitchhike.

185
00:12:02,807 --> 00:12:03,907
No problem.

186
00:12:04,107 --> 00:12:06,964
I'll wait for the guy
who's following us.

187
00:12:12,772 --> 00:12:15,765
- Something to drink?
- Nope.

188
00:12:16,107 --> 00:12:17,987
I have a girl friend like that.

189
00:12:18,107 --> 00:12:19,907
She never drinks while eating.

190
00:12:20,107 --> 00:12:21,741
She says it makes you fat.

191
00:12:21,861 --> 00:12:22,830
I don't believe it.

192
00:12:26,258 --> 00:12:28,837
Actually,
I will have a coffee.

193
00:12:30,755 --> 00:12:33,328
I am sure you're married,
with 5 kids.

194
00:12:33,528 --> 00:12:35,313
No.

195
00:12:39,197 --> 00:12:41,427
What about that coffee?

196
00:12:42,703 --> 00:12:45,481
In life, you need to go
after the things you want.

197
00:12:46,016 --> 00:12:47,852
Instead of waiting
for them to happen.

198
00:12:48,272 --> 00:12:49,914
What do you think?

199
00:12:53,224 --> 00:12:56,636
If everyone stays in their corner...

200
00:12:56,864 --> 00:12:58,651
without trying to communicate...

201
00:12:58,947 --> 00:12:59,928
it's the end.

202
00:13:02,772 --> 00:13:06,057
I am for communication.

203
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:08,288
Please.

204
00:13:10,578 --> 00:13:12,390
There is no need to be afraid of women.

205
00:13:12,929 --> 00:13:14,607
I've noticed that...

206
00:13:15,563 --> 00:13:18,571
When women know what they want
and say it...

207
00:13:19,176 --> 00:13:20,750
men get scared.

208
00:13:23,699 --> 00:13:25,310
What's gotten into you?

209
00:13:38,045 --> 00:13:39,560
Wait, wait!

210
00:15:08,421 --> 00:15:09,245
Sir!

211
00:15:12,013 --> 00:15:12,981
Good evening.

212
00:15:13,255 --> 00:15:13,996
Evening.

213
00:15:14,169 --> 00:15:15,329
Are you alone?

214
00:15:15,542 --> 00:15:16,672
Yes, alone.

215
00:15:17,089 --> 00:15:19,431
Why haven't you stopped before?

216
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:21,316
Where before?

217
00:15:21,431 --> 00:15:22,558
At the restaurant.

218
00:15:23,606 --> 00:15:25,339
What's wrong?

219
00:15:25,459 --> 00:15:26,714
Was I going too fast?

220
00:15:26,834 --> 00:15:28,050
No. Show me your papers.

221
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,301
My papers? Of course.

222
00:15:36,538 --> 00:15:37,187
Here.

223
00:15:48,332 --> 00:15:49,411
A pilot?

224
00:15:50,258 --> 00:15:51,067
You're a pilot?

225
00:15:51,762 --> 00:15:52,355
What?

226
00:15:53,130 --> 00:15:54,452
You are an airline pilot?

227
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:55,526
Yes.

228
00:15:55,971 --> 00:15:57,110
How do you know?

229
00:15:58,272 --> 00:15:59,753
This is a pilot's license.

230
00:16:00,232 --> 00:16:01,292
My mistake.

231
00:16:07,593 --> 00:16:09,484
Here is my driver's license.

232
00:16:11,273 --> 00:16:12,254
You're French?

233
00:16:12,835 --> 00:16:13,359
Yes.

234
00:16:14,395 --> 00:16:16,157
Show me your passport.

235
00:16:28,261 --> 00:16:29,508
Come with me.

236
00:16:31,749 --> 00:16:34,351
What have I done?

237
00:16:34,638 --> 00:16:35,635
Come with me.

238
00:18:18,017 --> 00:18:18,997
What's wrong?

239
00:18:19,431 --> 00:18:20,273
It's taking a long time.

240
00:18:24,598 --> 00:18:25,647
Open the glove compartment.

241
00:18:26,128 --> 00:18:26,903
What for?

242
00:18:27,472 --> 00:18:29,090
Open it and you'll see.

243
00:18:30,241 --> 00:18:31,734
I can't because of the seatbelt.

244
00:18:32,297 --> 00:18:33,785
Take off the seatbelt
for a moment.

245
00:18:36,261 --> 00:18:37,264
What do I do now?

246
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,705
Look inside the glove compartment.

247
00:18:40,706 --> 00:18:41,629
What do you see?

248
00:18:41,925 --> 00:18:46,005
Kleenex papers, tapes, and candies.

249
00:18:47,313 --> 00:18:49,228
Ah, you don't like candies.

250
00:18:49,810 --> 00:18:50,880
Have I offended you?

251
00:18:52,305 --> 00:18:53,136
Deeply.

252
00:18:55,236 --> 00:18:56,603
Sorry about that.

253
00:19:00,581 --> 00:19:01,978
Still offended?

254
00:19:02,404 --> 00:19:04,484
Stop fooling
and give me a candy.

255
00:19:07,251 --> 00:19:07,696
Here.

256
00:19:08,049 --> 00:19:08,659
Thanks.

257
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:10,174
You know you always say that?

258
00:19:10,448 --> 00:19:11,211
What?

259
00:19:11,331 --> 00:19:12,419
Stop fooling.

260
00:19:14,438 --> 00:19:15,304
Could be.

261
00:19:19,147 --> 00:19:21,177
Looking at your watch
won't make us go faster.

262
00:19:23,580 --> 00:19:25,027
Has he gone back?

263
00:19:26,452 --> 00:19:27,193
Too bad.

264
00:19:28,052 --> 00:19:28,758
Why bad?

265
00:19:29,852 --> 00:19:31,509
We will never know
what he wanted.

266
00:19:32,382 --> 00:19:33,837
All the better.

267
00:19:37,514 --> 00:19:38,814
I will bet you 1000 francs

268
00:19:38,934 --> 00:19:41,378
that I can calculate how many cars

269
00:19:41,498 --> 00:19:43,292
will pass by inside 5 minutes.

270
00:19:44,418 --> 00:19:45,876
Old or new francs?

271
00:19:46,150 --> 00:19:46,800
Old francs.

272
00:19:47,723 --> 00:19:48,509
Alright.

273
00:19:49,296 --> 00:19:50,127
Thirty five.

274
00:19:55,477 --> 00:19:57,608
Thirty three and seven over.

275
00:19:58,212 --> 00:19:58,679
Six.

276
00:19:59,260 --> 00:19:59,830
Five.

277
00:20:00,594 --> 00:20:01,310
Four.

278
00:20:02,222 --> 00:20:02,849
Three.

279
00:20:03,522 --> 00:20:04,126
Two.

280
00:20:05,028 --> 00:20:05,530
