He's doesn't have a file?

568
00:40:13,651 --> 00:40:14,736
Nothing at all?

569
00:40:19,301 --> 00:40:21,387
Did the lady report anything?

570
00:40:21,999 --> 00:40:23,605
She said he had a hard-on.

571
00:40:50,719 --> 00:40:51,846
It's the clutch?

572
00:40:52,798 --> 00:40:53,494
Yes.

573
00:40:54,069 --> 00:40:55,232
Do you have a carjack?

574
00:40:56,321 --> 00:40:57,146
Can I use your garage?

575
00:40:57,266 --> 00:40:59,016
Yes, but there is no mechanic.

576
00:40:59,136 --> 00:41:00,618
I don't need one.

577
00:41:09,156 --> 00:41:10,657
Do you have a size 11 wrench?

578
00:41:10,777 --> 00:41:11,501
Sure.

579
00:41:14,336 --> 00:41:15,007
Here.

580
00:41:15,459 --> 00:41:16,238
Thank you.

581
00:41:17,125 --> 00:41:18,216
You're French?

582
00:41:18,336 --> 00:41:18,959
Yes.

583
00:41:19,079 --> 00:41:19,738
Where from?

584
00:41:19,858 --> 00:41:20,577
Paris.

585
00:41:21,128 --> 00:41:22,027
You're going there?

586
00:41:22,363 --> 00:41:23,034
Yes.

587
00:41:23,538 --> 00:41:25,312
I am going to join my wife.

588
00:41:25,766 --> 00:41:26,857
She's already there.

589
00:41:28,991 --> 00:41:30,322
And my son.

590
00:41:30,442 --> 00:41:31,544
You have a son?

591
00:41:31,820 --> 00:41:34,469
No, but it's as if I did.

592
00:41:36,468 --> 00:41:37,583
It's her boy.

593
00:41:38,554 --> 00:41:40,208
From her first marriage.

594
00:41:41,167 --> 00:41:42,402
He's almost 12 years old.

595
00:41:42,905 --> 00:41:44,224
They're sweet at that age.

596
00:41:49,287 --> 00:41:51,547
I bet it's going to rain before tonight.

597
00:41:52,865 --> 00:41:53,753
No way.

598
00:41:56,867 --> 00:41:57,946
About the detour...

599
00:41:58,642 --> 00:42:00,236
You added only 25 km...

600
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:01,819
...before going back to the highway.

601
00:42:05,077 --> 00:42:05,820
So what?

602
00:42:06,767 --> 00:42:09,584
You never intended
to lose him for long.

603
00:42:10,543 --> 00:42:11,251
Never.

604
00:42:13,406 --> 00:42:14,761
You are a liar.

605
00:42:16,175 --> 00:42:17,638
I am a liar indeed.

606
00:42:19,088 --> 00:42:20,611
We'll be in France tonight.

607
00:42:20,863 --> 00:42:22,948
Tonight we'll make it to the border.

608
00:42:26,505 --> 00:42:28,495
Tonight, when we talk to mom...

609
00:42:28,615 --> 00:42:29,874
...we should not tell her.

610
00:42:30,210 --> 00:42:30,941
Really?

611
00:42:32,390 --> 00:42:34,416
I was planning to tell her everything.

612
00:42:41,162 --> 00:42:42,649
Do you often see your father?

613
00:42:43,140 --> 00:42:44,147
Almost never.

614
00:42:44,267 --> 00:42:45,274
It's better that way.

615
00:42:46,341 --> 00:42:46,988
Why?

616
00:42:47,935 --> 00:42:49,146
Because he has his family.

617
00:42:49,266 --> 00:42:51,112
Children from his new marriage.

618
00:42:51,830 --> 00:42:53,424
When I get there, it's a pain.

619
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,187
What do you mean?

620
00:42:56,565 --> 00:42:58,471
I remind him of a previous marriage...

621
00:42:58,591 --> 00:42:59,910
...and everyone gets upset.

622
00:43:01,709 --> 00:43:03,219
You've been married before?

623
00:43:03,339 --> 00:43:04,058
Yes.

624
00:43:05,209 --> 00:43:06,528
It didn't work out?

625
00:43:06,648 --> 00:43:07,247
It did.

626
00:43:08,769 --> 00:43:10,304
Why did you get a divorce then?

627
00:43:11,549 --> 00:43:12,652
I didn't.

628
00:43:14,222 --> 00:43:15,241
I don't understand.

629
00:43:15,361 --> 00:43:16,308
She died.

630
00:43:19,193 --> 00:43:21,482
Tell me if you need to go
to the bathroom.

631
00:43:21,914 --> 00:43:23,880
I am fine but I feel it coming soon...

632
00:43:30,442 --> 00:43:31,653
I don't understand.

633
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:34,134
You're not alone, little guy.

634
00:43:40,924 --> 00:43:42,015
Why are you laughing?

635
00:43:42,135 --> 00:43:43,741
Because they don't know
what to think.

636
00:43:44,916 --> 00:43:47,697
Even if they had discovered
that I know their hotels...

637
00:43:47,817 --> 00:43:50,910
...they have to get
to their planned destination.

638
00:43:51,737 --> 00:43:53,367
I did all I had to do.

639
00:43:54,374 --> 00:43:55,549
Why tonight?

640
00:43:55,801 --> 00:43:57,875
It's less risky at the hotel.

641
00:43:58,102 --> 00:43:59,169
It's better.

642
00:44:00,317 --> 00:44:01,791
Isn't that clever?

643
00:44:02,487 --> 00:44:03,637
I am clever, huh?

644
00:44:04,824 --> 00:44:05,496
You are.

645
00:44:06,802 --> 00:44:08,373
You should not have left me.

646
00:44:09,636 --> 00:44:12,429
Say it,
that you never should've left...

647
00:44:12,933 --> 00:44:14,527
I should never have left you.

648
00:44:15,384 --> 00:44:17,914
You should never have
moved to Paris.

649
00:44:55,812 --> 00:44:58,941
Lucky you parked near the motel!

650
00:44:59,061 --> 00:45:01,314
I didn't know it was the entrance
of the restaurant.

651
00:45:05,095 --> 00:45:06,869
You look funny.

652
00:45:06,989 --> 00:45:08,248
Did you see yourself?

653
00:45:48,004 --> 00:45:48,759
Hello?

654
00:45:48,879 --> 00:45:49,551
3606 ?

655
00:45:49,671 --> 00:45:50,246
Yes!

656
00:45:50,366 --> 00:45:51,660
Hold the line.

657
00:45:52,942 --> 00:45:53,674
Mom?

658
00:45:53,946 --> 00:45:54,881
Marc?

659
00:45:55,109 --> 00:45:56,368
How are you?

660
00:45:56,715 --> 00:45:58,106
Did you arrive safely?

661
00:45:58,525 --> 00:45:59,317
Yeah.

662
00:45:59,988 --> 00:46:01,319
Without a problem.

663
00:46:05,024 --> 00:46:06,763
You're not very talkative...

664
00:46:07,338 --> 00:46:08,165
Me?

665
00:46:08,813 --> 00:46:10,443
Do you have a headache?

666
00:46:11,294 --> 00:46:12,745
Did you catch a cold?

667
00:46:14,774 --> 00:46:16,872
Give me Alex.
Kisses!

668
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:19,210
Kisses. Here he is.

669
00:46:21,236 --> 00:46:22,087
Nicole?

670
00:46:22,518 --> 00:46:23,729
What is going on?

671
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:28,008
Nothing! We drove all day,
we are both tired.

672
00:46:28,363 --> 00:46:29,706
What's up with you?

673
00:46:30,299 --> 00:46:33,595
The furniture arrived.
The couch doesn't open.

674
00:46:34,003 --> 00:46:35,909
We'll need more furniture though.

675
00:46:36,868 --> 00:46:40,752
There's a bed, a table, chairs...
You'll see.

676
00:46:41,243 --> 00:46:42,382
I miss you.

677
00:46:42,790 --> 00:46:43,749
Me too.

678
00:46:43,869 --> 00:46:44,840
I love you.

679
00:46:45,691 --> 00:46:46,638
Me too.

680
00:46:48,573 --> 00:46:50,312
All I do is wait.

681
00:46:51,079 --> 00:46:52,350
I wish you'd arrived already.

682
00:46:52,685 --> 00:46:53,608
Me too!

683
00:46:53,728 --> 00:46:56,497
Don't say the same thing all the time.

684
00:46:56,903 --> 00:46:57,742
Wait...

685
00:46:57,970 --> 00:46:59,361
Why don't you go take a leak?

686
00:46:59,481 --> 00:47:00,901
Why?
I don't need to!

687
00:47:01,021 --> 00:47:03,059
Maybe you could try?

688
00:47:03,765 --> 00:47:06,606
Are you insane?
I am old enough to know when to go.

689
00:47:09,315 --> 00:47:11,425
Ah, now I understand!

690
00:47:11,874 --> 00:47:13,277
Don't be too long, ok?

691
00:47:16,525 --> 00:47:17,532
Come on!

692
00:47:24,423 --> 00:47:25,466
Still there?

693
00:47:26,639 --> 00:47:28,521
I got rid of your creature.

694
00:47:28,641 --> 00:47:30,056
What do you mean "my creature"?

695
00:47:31,291 --> 00:47:34,156
Alex, home is empty without you two.

696
00:47:34,741 --> 00:47:36,359
I want you so much...

697
00:47:37,042 --> 00:47:37,989
Me too.

698
00:47:38,289 --> 00:47:39,392
Here you go again.

699
00:47:39,704 --> 00:47:43,336
What good it did to get rid of the boy.

700
00:47:44,837 --> 00:47:46,563
Sorry, I am doing my best.

701
00:47:48,769 --> 00:47:49,980
I want you...

702
00:47:50,448 --> 00:47:51,491
Me too...

703
00:47:59,274 --> 00:48:01,660
Is it true that all is well
with the kid?

704
00:48:01,780 --> 00:48:03,746
He's perfectly OK,
why?

705
00:48:04,381 --> 00:48:06,539
There was something in his voice...

706
00:48:06,997 --> 00:48:08,951
Maybe I am getting ideas...

707
00:48:09,443 --> 00:48:12,691
No need to worry,
he's doing very well.

708
00:48:14,993 --> 00:48:16,072
Good night.

709
00:48:16,388 --> 00:48:17,371
Kisses.

710
00:48:18,103 --> 00:48:19,193
Kisses.

711
00:48:21,315 --> 00:48:22,670
See you tomorrow.

712
00:48:39,386 --> 00:48:40,717
Are you asleep?

713
00:48:41,101 --> 00:48:41,820
Yes.

714
00:48:42,671 --> 00:48:44,134
You should be too.

715
00:48:46,172 --> 00:48:48,497
She sensed there was something wrong.

716
00:48:51,093 --> 00:48:54,606
It's always been that way.
I could never hide anything from her.

717
00:48:55,085 --> 00:48:56,943
I wonder how she does it.

718
00:48:57,351 --> 00:48:58,765
She doesn't know herself.

719
00:48:58,885 --> 00:48:59,740
What?

720
00:49:00,160 --> 00:49:02,389
She doesn't know
how she does it.

721
00:49:04,176 --> 00:49:06,106
An animal in the woods...

722
00:49:07,172 --> 00:49:10,228
Suddenly, it raises its head
and runs to hide...

723
00:49:11,056 --> 00:49:13,237
Way before anything happens...

724
00:49:14,340 --> 00:49:16,510
Because it senses danger.

725
00:49:19,015 --> 00:49:22,396
This can't be explained,
it just knows by instinct.

726
00:49:22,803 --> 00:49:25,379
But she's 1500 km away from here...

727
00:49:26,626 --> 00:49:27,717
You see...

728
00:49:29,683 --> 00:49:31,852
it's the same thing - she just knows.

729
00:49:34,308 --> 00:49:35,111
Say...

730
00:49:37,399 --> 00:49:39,020
Do you think we lost him?

731
00:49:41,069 --> 00:49:41,764
Yes.

732
00:49:45,181 --> 00:49:47,627
The last time we also believed that.

733
00:49:48,706 --> 00:49:50,240
This time we lost him.

734
00:49:50,761 --> 00:49:51,732
Go to sleep.

735
00:49:53,794 --> 00:49:55,412
What did he want from us?

736
00:49:56,479 --> 00:49:57,702
We'll never know.

737
00:49:59,225 --> 00:50:00,567
Go to sleep, kid.

738
00:50:00,956 --> 00:50:02,119
Yes, sir.

739
00:50:06,866 --> 00:50:08,485
It's raining buckets...

740
00:50:29,449 --> 00:50:30,792
They're all dead...

741
00:50:49,888 --> 00:50:52,369
This is a cartridge from the mother's room.

742
00:51:24,864 --> 00:51:28,245
I am looking for a guy
who killed two policemen.

743
00:51:28,365 --> 00:51:29,360
There's no connection.

744
00:51:30,354 --> 00:51:31,468
How do you know?

745
00:51:31,588 --> 00:51:33,003
This is a family murder.

746
00:51:33,123 --> 00:51:34,190
A father...

747
00:51:34,681 --> 00:51:35,604
Father?

748
00:51:36,168 --> 00:51:37,846
A father killed his entire family?

749
00:51:37,966 --> 00:51:40,722
His children, his wife...
and himself.

750
00:51:41,297 --> 00:51:42,065
Why?

751
00:51:42,796 --> 00:51:45,505
He left a note...
of religious character.

752
00:51:45,625 --> 00:51:50,777
His son was a junkie, his daughter a slut -
and the wife gave birth to that.

753
00:51:51,856 --> 00:51:53,247
Couldn't it be true?

754
00:51:54,086 --> 00:51:54,937
Sure.

755
00:52:05,105 --> 00:52:06,580
A cutie, eh?

756
00:52:08,042 --> 00:52:09,876
My daughter is her age...

757
00:53:01,930 --> 00:53:02,745
Alex!

758
00:53:11,179 --> 00:53:12,006
Alex!

759
00:53:13,995 --> 00:53:17,040
Someone is trying to force the lock.

760
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:18,088
Listen!

761
00:53:19,359 --> 00:53:20,366
Do you hear?

762
00:53:20,979 --> 00:53:22,046
It must be him.

763
00:53:48,837 --> 00:53:51,630
Lock the door
and don't let anyone in!

764
00:53:52,798 --> 00:53:53,697
Got that?

765
00:53:55,053 --> 00:53:56,299
When I am back...

766
00:53:56,707 --> 00:53:58,697
Make me talk
to make sure it's me.

767
00:53:59,177 --> 00:53:59,836
Ok.

768
00:54:00,410 --> 00:54:02,017
Lock the door after me.

769
00:54:03,000 --> 00:54:03,971
I must hear it.

770
00:54:04,474 --> 00:54:05,649
Be careful, Alex!

771
00:56:12,106 --> 00:56:13,436
What do you want?

772
00:56:14,359 --> 00:56:15,318
Who are you?

773
00:56:16,601 --> 00:56:17,920
What do you want?

774
00:57:27,941 --> 00:57:31,537
If I understood correctly,
you have no explanation to offer?

775
00:57:31,657 --> 00:57:32,628
None at all.

776
00:57:33,226 --> 00:57:35,875
You have never seen that man before,

777
00:57:35,995 --> 00:57:37,602
and don't know who he might be.

778
00:57:38,092 --> 00:57:39,867
For the fifth time : no!

779
00:57:40,599 --> 00:57:42,733
You don't make things easy for me.

780
00:57:43,297 --> 00:57:44,376
I'll be going.

781
00:57:44,867 --> 00:57:46,629
What will you do?

782
00:57:46,749 --> 00:57:48,811
The usual : search for the suspect.

783
00:57:48,931 --> 00:57:49,746
What do you want?

784
00:57:49,866 --> 00:57:50,993
I want police protection.

785
00:57:51,455 --> 00:57:54,488
I want an agent next to our door
until we depart.

786
00:57:54,608 --> 00:57:58,239
I want motorcyclists
to escort us to the border.

787
00:57:58,359 --> 00:57:59,174
But...

788
00:57:59,294 --> 00:58:00,277
No buts!

789
00:58:00,726 --> 00:58:02,177
We'll do our best.

790
00:58:02,464 --> 00:58:03,208
Thanks.

791
00:58:04,310 --> 00:58:05,389
Feeling better?

792
00:58:06,287 --> 00:58:07,929
Take this for pain.

793
00:58:08,169 --> 00:58:11,298
Not more than twice a day.
Do not leave too early.

794
00:58:11,418 --> 00:58:12,665
Thank you doctor.

795
00:58:16,176 --> 00:58:17,267
So, kid?

796
00:58:17,650 --> 00:58:18,897
Don't look sour!

797
00:58:19,490 --> 00:58:20,761
I am still here!

798
00:58:59,939 --> 00:59:00,874
Mister Moineau?

799
00:59:00,994 --> 00:59:01,630
Yes.

800
00:59:01,941 --> 00:59:03,644
Inspector Boetani, federal police.

801
00:59:03,764 --> 00:59:05,514
We've already seen policemen...

802
00:59:06,346 --> 00:59:08,660
I know.
I drove 700 km to talk to you.

803
00:59:09,691 --> 00:59:10,938
Two policemen have been...

804
00:59:13,486 --> 00:59:16,519
Two policemen were shot
on the highway yesterday.

805
00:59:16,986 --> 00:59:18,748
You think it's the same guy?

806
00:59:19,312 --> 00:59:20,618
I know it.

807
00:59:21,158 --> 00:59:22,465
Everything fits.

808
00:59:23,051 --> 00:59:25,017
Because if it was different guys...

809
00:59:25,251 --> 00:59:28,440
...who could possibly believe that.

810
00:59:31,194 --> 00:59:32,237
Your son?

811
00:59:32,357 --> 00:59:33,544
My wife's son.

812
00:59:35,510 --> 00:59:37,764
Please, take a seat.

813
00:59:42,013 --> 00:59:44,051
What would you like to know?

814
00:59:44,435 --> 00:59:46,137
Why was he following you?

815
00:59:46,461 --> 00:59:48,127
Why did he try to kill you?

816
00:59:48,247 --> 00:59:49,314
I don't know.

817
00:59:49,636 --> 00:59:51,554
I've never seen this man before.

818
00:59:51,674 --> 00:59:52,813
Are you sure?

819
00:59:52,933 --> 00:59:53,868
Positive.

820
00:59:55,464 --> 00:59:56,663
And the kid?

821
00:59:56,927 --> 00:59:58,521
The kid didn't see him.

822
00:59:59,671 --> 01:00:03,615
It's not because you don't know him
that he doesn't know you.

823
01:00:04,274 --> 01:00:05,533
What do you mean?

824
01:00:07,126 --> 01:00:08,696
May I see your passport?

825
01:00:08,816 --> 01:00:10,123
I've already...

826
01:00:10,243 --> 01:00:11,789
Please!

827
01:00:41,116 --> 01:00:44,054
In the last eight years...

828
01:00:44,293 --> 01:00:46,175
...you've been...

829
01:00:47,182 --> 01:00:50,060
...13 times to Algeria.

830
01:00:50,650 --> 01:00:54,439
I work for a company
that does business there.

831
01:00:57,069 --> 01:01:00,126
Are you involved with politics,
Mister Moineau?

832
01:01:00,527 --> 01:01:01,894
What do you mean?

833
01:01:03,002 --> 01:01:06,467
Do you have party membership,
a right-wing party?

834
01:01:07,755 --> 01:01:08,462
No.

835
01:01:09,122 --> 01:01:10,248
What's the connection?

836
01:01:10,368 --> 01:01:11,687
Are you sure?

837
01:01:12,453 --> 01:01:14,611
Where were you
during the Algerian war?

838
01:01:15,078 --> 01:01:16,637
In Paris, and in Rome.

839
01:01:16,978 --> 01:01:18,836
Forgive me for insisting...

840
01:01:19,160 --> 01:01:22,055
...what about OAS?
Not even a little?

841
01:01:22,546 --> 01:01:24,668
This conversation is getting...

842
01:01:26,946 --> 01:01:28,180
Don't get upset.

843
01:01:28,940 --> 01:01:30,954
I was in Paris in 1960.

844
01:01:32,069 --> 01:01:33,604
I remember it all.

845
01:01:34,580 --> 01:01:36,007
And I am not alone.

846
01:01:37,858 --> 01:01:41,298
You said an unknown man
tried to kill you.

847
01:01:41,418 --> 01:01:43,120
I am trying to understand why.

848
01:01:43,791 --> 01:01:45,254
What if there's no reason?

849
01:01:45,374 --> 01:01:46,525
It's possible.

850
01:01:47,309 --> 01:01:48,832
Everything is possible.

851
01:01:50,023 --> 01:01:51,136
But it's improbable.

852
01:01:51,411 --> 01:01:52,981
Why kill the policemen?

853
01:01:53,101 --> 01:01:54,000
Who knows!

854
01:01:54,802 --> 01:01:56,732
I was counting on you to tell me.

855
01:01:56,852 --> 01:01:59,021
I've never seen this guy before.

856
01:01:59,261 --> 01:02:00,615
I don't do politics.

857
01:02:00,735 --> 01:02:02,138
I have no enemies.

858
01:02:02,258 --> 01:02:05,062
And I don't understand
why he tried to kill me.

859
01:02:06,045 --> 01:02:09,353
Violence doesn't just happen
one fine morning.

860
01:02:10,276 --> 01:02:13,002
And God has not chosen you
out of the blue.

861
01:02:14,998 --> 01:02:17,731
I will be able to offer you protection...

862
01:02:18,185 --> 01:02:20,404
once I know what's it about.

863
01:02:21,074 --> 01:02:24,443
I am sorry, inspector,
but I have a long way to go tomorrow....

864
01:02:24,903 --> 01:02:26,917
and I need to rest.

865
01:02:27,600 --> 01:02:28,787
Mister Moineau!

866
01:02:30,561 --> 01:02:32,539
Have you ever been incarcerated?

867
01:02:34,891 --> 01:02:35,886
You never know.

868
01:02:38,319 --> 01:02:39,314
You're not sleeping?

869
01:02:39,902 --> 01:02:41,220
I was listening to you.

870
01:02:44,325 --> 01:02:45,236
Back to bed!

871
01:02:53,472 --> 01:02:55,557
He has a point, you know...

872
01:02:55,953 --> 01:02:56,960
How so?

873
01:02:57,931 --> 01:03:00,436
It's true that we weren't chosen
by chance.

874
01:03:01,335 --> 01:03:02,486
There must be a reason.

875
01:03:04,702 --> 01:03:05,457
I know.

876
01:03:17,650 --> 01:03:18,465
Slept well?

877
01:03:18,585 --> 01:03:19,185
No.

878
01:03:19,940 --> 01:03:21,894
Where are the motorcyclists?

879
01:03:22,014 --> 01:03:22,973
Motorcyclists?

880
01:03:23,284 --> 01:03:25,706
I asked to be escorted to the border.

881
01:03:26,123 --> 01:03:27,526
Yes of course.

882
01:03:27,849 --> 01:03:28,689
I cancelled them.

883
01:03:29,084 --> 01:03:30,283
What do you mean?

884
01:03:30,403 --> 01:03:31,769
You didn't tell me anything.

885
01:03:31,889 --> 01:03:34,165
Give me a reason
and I'll protect you.

886
01:03:34,285 --> 01:03:35,568
You get nothing
if you give nothing.

887
01:03:36,515 --> 01:03:37,210
Fine!

888
01:03:37,330 --> 01:03:38,661
I'll call my embassy.

889
01:03:38,781 --> 01:03:40,003
It's useless.

890
01:03:41,465 --> 01:03:42,220
He's dead.

891
01:03:43,647 --> 01:03:44,462
The ambassador?

892
01:03:45,217 --> 01:03:46,967
The guy who followed you.

893
01:03:47,339 --> 01:03:48,646
We found his car.

894
01:03:48,905 --> 01:03:51,422
Not far from here at 6 am,
burned.

895
01:03:52,609 --> 01:03:54,288
The guy burned inside.

896
01:03:54,959 --> 01:03:56,098
Are you sure of that?

897
01:03:56,326 --> 01:03:57,261
Absolutely.

898
01:03:58,399 --> 01:03:59,814
You should have said so.

899
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:02,110
I wanted to surprise you.

900
01:04:05,515 --> 01:04:08,047
You still don't want to tell me
why he followed you?

901
01:04:16,648 --> 01:04:17,355
Know what?

902
01:04:17,907 --> 01:04:19,034
I am so relieved.

903
01:04:19,154 --> 01:04:20,400
You bet. Me too!

904
01:04:21,947 --> 01:04:25,028
A guy dies and we're happy?
Not nice but...

905
01:04:25,148 --> 01:04:26,737
It's just the way it is.

906
01:04:26,857 --> 01:04:28,500
Coming back from Saint-Malo...

907
01:04:29,998 --> 01:04:31,521
I met three camels...

908
01:04:33,052 --> 01:04:34,706
I put them in my bed...

909
01:04:36,037 --> 01:04:38,201
And, mom, I loved some tit...

910
01:04:39,088 --> 01:04:42,468
They have round hats,
long live Bretons!

911
01:04:45,748 --> 01:04:47,354
Coming back from Saint-Martin...

912
01:04:48,739 --> 01:04:50,381
I found three little rabbits...

913
01:04:51,579 --> 01:04:53,353
I put them inside my slip...

914
01:04:54,839 --> 01:04:57,453
And they ate my little carrot.

915
01:05:04,757 --> 01:05:06,543
Coming back from Saint-Quentin...

916
01:05:08,376 --> 01:05:10,821
I found three little sluts...

917
01:05:13,553 --> 01:05:17,030
I put them in my pocket...

918
01:05:17,567 --> 01:05:19,089
And they ate my little noodle...

919
01:06:03,017 --> 01:06:04,228
Personal belongings?

920
01:06:04,348 --> 01:06:06,422
All the papers were burnt.

921
01:06:07,727 --> 01:06:10,053
A watch, two rings, a bracelet.

922
01:06:12,295 --> 01:06:13,846
I knew it was a fag.

923
01:06:25,960 --> 01:06:28,718
Ah you were good looking
in your youth!

924
01:06:28,838 --> 01:06:30,048
Don't push it.

925
01:06:30,875 --> 01:06:32,973
You didn't wear glasses.

926
01:06:33,089 --> 01:06:35,462
I took them off for the photo.

927
01:06:35,738 --> 01:06:36,697
Why?

928
01:06:36,937 --> 01:06:38,220
You don't like glasses?

929
01:06:38,340 --> 01:06:39,251
No reason.

930
01:06:39,634 --> 01:06:42,499
We'll see what we can do
about contact lenses.

931
01:06:42,989 --> 01:06:44,224
It must be possible.

932
01:06:44,344 --> 01:06:45,686
Passports please.

933
01:07:00,417 --> 01:07:01,244
Easy!

934
01:07:03,570 --> 01:07:04,397
Good!

935
01:07:15,074 --> 01:07:17,843
A potato baked in the ashes.
You like?

936
01:07:19,329 --> 01:07:22,254
It's from this car's blaze.

937
01:07:22,542 --> 01:07:23,585
A homosexual farmer!

938
01:07:24,024 --> 01:07:26,134
We're dealing with a rustic fag.

939
01:07:40,566 --> 01:07:43,096
How long is this tunnel?

940
01:07:43,216 --> 01:07:44,486
I've no idea.

941
01:07:47,720 --> 01:07:49,099
Do you have a trip counter?

942
01:07:49,219 --> 01:07:49,890
I do.

943
01:07:50,190 --> 01:07:51,377
Switch it on.

944
01:07:51,844 --> 01:07:52,587
Done.

945
01:07:52,851 --> 01:07:53,701
What now?

946
01:07:53,821 --> 01:07:55,811
I will bet on 20 km.

947
01:07:56,326 --> 01:07:57,225
How much?

948
01:07:57,345 --> 01:07:58,352
Fifty francs.

949
01:07:58,592 --> 01:07:59,587
Old money?

950
01:07:59,707 --> 01:08:00,977
You must be kidding.

951
01:08:01,097 --> 01:08:02,116
I accept.

952
01:08:04,860 --> 01:08:08,504
Did you ask about the tunnel
to test me or because you didn't know?

953
01:08:09,066 --> 01:08:10,265
What do you mean?

954
01:08:10,385 --> 01:08:11,919
You might have read about it.

955
01:08:12,171 --> 01:08:13,610
That wouldn't be fair play.

956
01:08:13,730 --> 01:08:14,772
Oh really?

957
01:08:14,892 --> 01:08:16,475
I swear I didn't know...

958
01:08:18,811 --> 01:08:22,724
Take off your seatbelt!
Lie down in the back!

959
01:08:29,275 --> 01:08:30,593
Between the seats!

960
01:08:46,130 --> 01:08:47,305
Don't look!

961
01:09:10,841 --> 01:09:12,207
Stay down!

962
01:10:00,923 --> 01:10:01,966
Stay down!

963
01:11:24,721 --> 01:11:26,075
Stay down!

964
01:11:32,850 --> 01:11:33,870
Marc, lie down!

965
01:12:38,578 --> 01:12:42,978
It was a Ford van.
They thought it was him...

966
01:12:43,601 --> 01:12:44,488
and we left.

967
01:12:44,608 --> 01:12:45,590
Incredible!

968
01:12:49,546 --> 01:12:51,680
How come the plates are from Rome?

969
01:12:51,991 --> 01:12:54,137
It's my wife's car,
she lived there.

970
01:12:56,078 --> 01:12:57,025
Incredible!

971
01:12:58,343 --> 01:12:59,722
It's your daughter?

972
01:13:00,010 --> 01:13:01,592
It's my wife's son.

973
01:13:02,694 --> 01:13:04,469
Hard to know these days.

974
01:13:04,589 --> 01:13:09,959
You think a girl is speeding,
you stop them and it's boys!

975
01:13:10,079 --> 01:13:11,193
You're ok?

976
01:13:12,699 --> 01:13:14,282
You got off easy...

977
01:13:15,085 --> 01:13:16,404
What a sight!

978
01:13:16,967 --> 01:13:18,646
Come to the office.

979
01:13:36,651 --> 01:13:37,933
Do you have insurance?

980
01:13:39,012 --> 01:13:40,127
For road accidents.

981
01:13:40,570 --> 01:13:42,910
What's the connection?
You've spoken to Italian police...

982
01:13:43,170 --> 01:13:45,430
They've confirmed your story.

983
01:13:46,131 --> 01:13:46,887
So?

984
01:13:47,774 --> 01:13:50,829
They've closed your file.

985
01:13:50,949 --> 01:13:52,030
The guy is dead.

986
01:13:52,290 --> 01:13:56,044
But he just attacked us!
The kid is my witness.

987
01:13:56,520 --> 01:13:59,014
Italian police saw him dead.

988
01:13:59,360 --> 01:14:02,501
You left and now
you got into an accident.

989
01:14:02,788 --> 01:14:06,037
I don't want to get involved in your
insurance schemes.

990
01:14:06,157 --> 01:14:07,350
Give me that phone.

991
01:14:07,610 --> 01:14:08,230
Why?

992
01:14:08,490 --> 01:14:09,150
To call the police.

993
01:14:09,410 --> 01:14:10,219
I am the police!

994
01:14:10,339 --> 01:14:11,087
You're incompetent!

995
01:14:11,207 --> 01:14:13,123
Don't touch the phone!

996
01:14:13,356 --> 01:14:14,769
I will call from elsewhere!

997
01:14:14,889 --> 01:14:16,783
No one will believe you!
You know it.

998
01:14:16,903 --> 01:14:19,194
Or they will refer you back to me...

999
01:14:19,314 --> 01:14:21,628
Because it happened in my district!

1000
01:14:21,748 --> 01:14:25,512
If it wasn't for your daughter,
I'd arrest you to calm you down!

1001
01:14:25,632 --> 01:14:29,276
You can call the Prefect
or the Pope!

1002
01:14:29,396 --> 01:14:31,732
You'll still have to deal with me!

1003
01:14:33,854 --> 01:14:34,777
Let's go!

1004
01:14:39,407 --> 01:14:40,834
Look at him!

1005
01:14:42,464 --> 01:14:43,411
You'll leave it there?

1006
01:14:43,663 --> 01:14:46,731
What else can we do?
No one will believe us.

1007
01:14:47,905 --> 01:14:48,684
Let's go!

1008
01:14:49,212 --> 01:14:51,130
We need a new windshield.

1009
01:15:21,556 --> 01:15:22,647
Do they have one?

1010
01:15:22,767 --> 01:15:23,762
Out of stock.

1011
01:15:26,115 --> 01:15:27,530
What are you doing?

1012
01:15:27,781 --> 01:15:29,292
We need to be warm.

1013
01:15:31,510 --> 01:15:32,157
Here!

1014
01:15:34,183 --> 01:15:35,514
Put that on too.

1015
01:16:14,811 --> 01:16:15,554
Hello?

1016
01:16:15,674 --> 01:16:16,585
Nicole!

1017
01:16:17,938 --> 01:16:18,981
I have great news!

1018
01:16:19,736 --> 01:16:20,588
Me too!

1019
01:16:21,091 --> 01:16:22,110
Tell me first!

1020
01:16:22,348 --> 01:16:23,523
No, you go first.

1021
01:16:24,170 --> 01:16:27,263
I am starting work on the 1st,
we'll have 8 days together.

1022
01:16:27,767 --> 01:16:28,798
Are you happy?

1023
01:16:28,918 --> 01:16:29,685
Very!

1024
01:16:30,115 --> 01:16:31,158
Listen...

1025
01:16:31,278 --> 01:16:33,448
Hey there guys!

1026
01:16:33,568 --> 01:16:36,229
What's that?
You're not at a hotel?

1027
01:16:36,683 --> 01:16:38,349
That's the thing...

1028
01:16:38,817 --> 01:16:41,694
We decided to go directly to Paris.

1029
01:16:41,814 --> 01:16:44,174
I thought you didn't want
to drive at night.

1030
01:16:45,109 --> 01:16:47,735
We miss you too much.

1031
01:16:47,855 --> 01:16:50,528
And I'm not at all sleepy.

1032
01:16:50,827 --> 01:16:53,908
We should get there at 3am.

1033
01:16:55,825 --> 01:16:56,903
What do you say?

1034
01:16:58,282 --> 01:17:01,159
The boy will sleep in the car.

1035
01:17:01,702 --> 01:17:04,184
It's true he can sleep anywhere.

1036
01:17:04,304 --> 01:17:05,526
Precisely.

1037
01:17:06,388 --> 01:17:08,176
I'll warm the bed for you...

1038
01:17:08,486 --> 01:17:10,464
I'll put the kid on...

1039
01:17:10,584 --> 01:17:12,921
You always flee
when I become tender...

1040
01:17:15,618 --> 01:17:16,590
Mom?

1041
01:17:17,359 --> 01:17:18,354
How are you?

1042
01:17:19,050 --> 01:17:21,327
So you confirm he's not sleepy?

1043
01:17:21,447 --> 01:17:23,221
We're both in top shape!

1044
01:17:23,647 --> 01:17:24,857
Don't worry!

1045
01:17:24,977 --> 01:17:26,020
Be careful!

1046
01:17:26,140 --> 01:17:28,502
I'll scold him if he takes risks.

1047
01:17:31,751 --> 01:17:32,566
Bye mom!

1048
01:17:33,717 --> 01:17:35,551
Many kisses!
Bye mom.

1049
01:17:42,535 --> 01:17:43,314
You're done?

1050
01:17:43,709 --> 01:17:44,548
Done.

1051
01:17:46,395 --> 01:17:47,246
Hot chocolate...

1052
01:17:48,228 --> 01:17:49,211
One coffee...

1053
01:17:50,104 --> 01:17:51,254
Call to Paris...

1054
01:17:52,902 --> 01:17:54,460
Can I ask you something?

1055
01:17:55,562 --> 01:17:57,048
Why drive all night?

1056
01:17:57,168 --> 01:17:59,710
The sooner we get to Paris,
the better.

1057
01:17:59,830 --> 01:18:01,530
That's the only reason?

1058
01:18:01,650 --> 01:18:03,796
Yes.
Can you think of another?

1059
01:18:04,755 --> 01:18:06,146
Try again!

1060
01:18:08,266 --> 01:18:09,129
Come in!

1061
01:18:10,861 --> 01:18:12,275
You know,
that fag of yours...

1062
01:18:13,197 --> 01:18:15,151
I have the proof
it is not him.

1063
01:18:15,271 --> 01:18:16,002
Not him?

1064
01:18:16,122 --> 01:18:19,095
We found a finger
less damaged by the fire.

1065
01:18:19,215 --> 01:18:21,229
The fingertips don't match.

1066
01:18:22,031 --> 01:18:27,365
Connect me to the police of
Grenoble, Lyon, Vintimille, Dijon, Paris...

1067
01:18:27,845 --> 01:18:29,715
and Interpol in Rome!

1068
01:18:45,653 --> 01:18:46,972
Don't fall asleep!

1069
01:18:57,222 --> 01:18:58,361
Let's try singing...

1070
01:18:58,820 --> 01:18:59,527
No.

1071
01:19:00,223 --> 01:19:02,189
I can't, I am too cold.

1072
01:19:04,478 --> 01:19:05,479
Please repeat...

1073
01:19:05,599 --> 01:19:08,320
I don't have the man's description
or the car's number.

1074
01:19:08,846 --> 01:19:11,639
But a Mister Moineau
is driving to Paris...

1075
01:19:12,441 --> 01:19:14,479
I believe it's a political case.

1076
01:19:14,599 --> 01:19:15,414
Moineau?

1077
01:19:15,810 --> 01:19:17,752
That's all?
What about his car?

1078
01:19:17,872 --> 01:19:19,944
A blue Renault 5
registered in Rome.

1079
01:19:20,064 --> 01:19:22,318
They must have crossed the border
this afternoon.

1080
01:19:22,988 --> 01:19:24,894
Try to determine their route...

1081
01:19:25,014 --> 01:19:27,723
Boulard is already on the case...

1082
01:19:29,748 --> 01:19:30,911
Give me Victor...

1083
01:19:31,174 --> 01:19:32,085
Boulard.

1084
01:19:33,859 --> 01:19:36,305
- I got the gendarmes.
- Let me talk to that fool.

1085
01:19:36,627 --> 01:19:38,245
The incident happened at 2pm.

1086
01:19:38,904 --> 01:19:41,482
It was a blue Renault
and a kid inside?

1087
01:19:42,331 --> 01:19:44,405
You didn't take the car's number
or it's destination?

1088
01:19:45,748 --> 01:19:47,534
But how could I know?

1089
01:19:48,192 --> 01:19:49,631
Do you remember the address?

1090
01:19:49,751 --> 01:19:52,963
On the license it was written
Alesia Street...

1091
01:19:53,957 --> 01:19:56,199
Alesia street.

1092
01:19:56,319 --> 01:19:57,542
House number?

1093
01:19:57,662 --> 01:19:59,676
I can't remember.

1094
01:20:13,532 --> 01:20:15,246
We found Moineau's address.

1095
01:20:15,366 --> 01:20:17,319
We couldn't reach him,
I sent a car.

1096
01:20:17,439 --> 01:20:19,177
What is this crazy story?

1097
01:20:19,297 --> 01:20:20,230
A complete mess...

1098
01:20:31,926 --> 01:20:33,569
You see, it's strange...

1099
01:20:34,094 --> 01:20:36,240
It's not as if I were asking
for the moon...

1100
01:20:37,571 --> 01:20:40,352
I only want to get back
what was taken from me...

1101
01:20:40,676 --> 01:20:41,551
That's all.

1102
01:20:42,206 --> 01:20:44,112
I'd like you to understand that.

1103
01:20:47,780 --> 01:20:49,087
I don't see you...

1104
01:21:12,798 --> 01:21:14,104
Nothing!

1105
01:21:17,413 --> 01:21:19,835
He moved three months ago...

1106
01:21:19,955 --> 01:21:22,291
Looks like he got married...

1107
01:21:23,358 --> 01:21:25,540
To a certain Letessier.

1108
01:21:26,193 --> 01:21:27,390
Nicole Letessier.

1109
01:23:08,095 --> 01:23:09,186
Fabio...

1110
01:23:10,157 --> 01:23:11,727
Don't say anything.

1111
01:23:17,636 --> 01:23:19,063
I am glad to see you.

1112
01:23:20,567 --> 01:23:22,005
Explain how...

1113
01:23:22,868 --> 01:23:25,662
Here I am,
I wanted to see you.

1114
01:23:26,530 --> 01:23:28,814
You drove from Rome
just to...

1115
01:23:28,934 --> 01:23:29,701
Yes!

1116
01:23:31,767 --> 01:23:33,182
What happened to you?

1117
01:23:33,547 --> 01:23:35,117
Oh it's nothing.

1118
01:23:35,237 --> 01:23:36,390
May I come in?

1119
01:23:40,866 --> 01:23:42,473
It's very nice.

1120
01:23:43,432 --> 01:23:44,379
Listen...

1121
01:23:44,499 --> 01:23:45,697
I'd rather you went...

1122
01:23:45,817 --> 01:23:48,830
I had to see you,
so I came!

1123
01:23:49,090 --> 01:23:51,072
Do you have something to eat?

1124
01:23:51,576 --> 01:23:52,310
Eat?

1125
01:23:53,866 --> 01:23:55,304
Yes, I am hungry.

1126
01:24:10,915 --> 01:24:12,101
Just a second!

1127
01:24:16,729 --> 01:24:18,084
Are you well covered?

1128
01:24:18,827 --> 01:24:20,169
Yeah, I am ok.

1129
01:24:44,677 --> 01:24:45,289
So?

1130
01:24:45,409 --> 01:24:46,943
She's in Rome.

1131
01:24:47,063 --> 01:24:48,945
She works for Air France there.

1132
01:24:49,783 --> 01:24:52,624
I don't care how late it is!

1133
01:24:52,744 --> 01:24:55,249
Find a Nicole Letessier,
in Rome,

1134
01:24:55,369 --> 01:24:56,567
She works for Air France.

1135
01:24:56,687 --> 01:24:59,085
And ask her if she's married
to a certain Moineau!

1136
01:25:17,351 --> 01:25:18,549
Would you like to buy it?

1137
01:25:19,100 --> 01:25:19,783
No.

1138
01:25:20,066 --> 01:25:22,272
With what I owe you
you can afford it.

1139
01:25:30,076 --> 01:25:31,947
What about this one?

1140
01:25:32,606 --> 01:25:33,565
Nope.

1141
01:25:42,020 --> 01:25:43,123
Alex, listen...

1142
01:25:45,183 --> 01:25:46,382
What is it, kid?

1143
01:25:47,845 --> 01:25:49,943
If it's going to go like this...

1144
01:25:50,350 --> 01:25:51,657
I won't make it.

1145
01:25:52,640 --> 01:25:53,683
You're cold?

1146
01:25:54,973 --> 01:25:56,196
It's not that...

1147
01:25:56,999 --> 01:25:59,073
I am talking about
something else.

1148
01:25:59,738 --> 01:26:00,877
What is it?

1149
01:26:03,181 --> 01:26:04,368
I am scared.

1150
01:26:08,264 --> 01:26:10,122
It's a knot in my stomach.

1151
01:26:12,830 --> 01:26:14,724
If this doesn't stop soon...

1152
01:26:14,844 --> 01:26:17,218
I won't be the same person.

1153
01:26:18,008 --> 01:26:19,159
Listen, kid...

1154
01:26:20,603 --> 01:26:22,497
You don't know
what people can withstand...

1155
01:26:23,634 --> 01:26:26,068
We've done 500 km
and he hasn't shown up.

1156
01:26:27,327 --> 01:26:29,387
There's only 100 km to go...

1157
01:26:30,071 --> 01:26:31,258
You'll make it.

1158
01:26:36,375 --> 01:26:37,910
Are you a fast runner?

1159
01:26:39,724 --> 01:26:40,492
Yeah.

1160
01:26:40,612 --> 01:26:43,045
I bet 1000 francs
that I can beat you over 100m.

1161
01:26:46,078 --> 01:26:47,097
Agreed.

1162
01:26:49,829 --> 01:26:51,627
We'll run to that column there.

1163
01:26:51,747 --> 01:26:55,595
We run around the column
and touch down there!

1164
01:26:56,721 --> 01:26:58,159
Let's start here!

1165
01:26:59,292 --> 01:26:59,940
One...

1166
01:27:01,018 --> 01:27:03,714
First I say: ready...
Go!

1167
01:27:12,151 --> 01:27:12,870
Cheater!

1168
01:27:24,138 --> 01:27:25,601
It does warm you up!

1169
01:27:26,152 --> 01:27:28,718
Not bad for a guy
who doesn't like sports...

1170
01:27:28,838 --> 01:27:29,953
Oh my!

1171
01:27:40,243 --> 01:27:41,430
Feeling better?

1172
01:27:41,910 --> 01:27:44,079
How long since you last ate?

1173
01:27:52,734 --> 01:27:53,705
Listen...

1174
01:27:55,036 --> 01:27:57,002
I know why you're here.

1175
01:28:01,729 --> 01:28:04,966
You called
and I told you I was leaving...

1176
01:28:07,411 --> 01:28:09,845
You wanted things back
as they were.

1177
01:28:11,424 --> 01:28:13,725
You suffered beyond words.

1178
01:28:16,638 --> 01:28:17,957
You still love me.

1179
01:28:18,221 --> 01:28:20,702
I am saying it
so you don't need to humiliate yourself.

1180
01:28:24,218 --> 01:28:26,688
But it's all over, Fabio.
It's over.

1181
01:28:27,719 --> 01:28:29,349
Since a long time.

1182
01:28:31,790 --> 01:28:34,140
I don't feel anything for you,
I'm sorry.

1183
01:28:37,173 --> 01:28:39,583
I'm married to a man I love.

1184
01:28:40,745 --> 01:28:42,016
You must understand.

1185
01:28:43,850 --> 01:28:44,641
No.

1186
01:28:46,319 --> 01:28:47,446
Why no?

1187
01:28:47,722 --> 01:28:49,364
No, I can't understand.

1188
01:28:50,407 --> 01:28:52,050
We were fine together.

1189
01:28:52,563 --> 01:28:55,045
You said everything would be
like before...

1190
01:28:57,430 --> 01:28:59,109
That I could touch you...

1191
01:29:02,993 --> 01:29:04,264
Kiss you...

1192
01:29:05,355 --> 01:29:06,386
I never said that...

1193
01:29:06,506 --> 01:29:07,309
You did!

1194
01:29:07,818 --> 01:29:09,329
In the van, you did!

1195
01:29:09,449 --> 01:29:10,575
What van?

1196
01:29:10,695 --> 01:29:12,222
Driving up here...

1197
01:29:13,505 --> 01:29:16,382
You can't say it's over
when you know it's not!

1198
01:29:20,696 --> 01:29:22,565
You still get those headaches?

1199
01:29:23,164 --> 01:29:25,466
Have you been to a doctor,
like I asked?

1200
01:29:25,586 --> 01:29:26,796
You're my doctor.

1201
01:29:30,558 --> 01:29:31,685
I said no!

1202
01:29:34,982 --> 01:29:36,600
You're even prettier
than before.

1203
01:29:37,847 --> 01:29:39,849
My husband will arrive soon.

1204
01:29:40,687 --> 01:29:41,598
How do you know?

1205
01:29:41,718 --> 01:29:43,048
He did that to me.

1206
01:29:43,816 --> 01:29:45,206
What are you saying?

1207
01:29:45,326 --> 01:29:47,556
Don't worry,
we'll take care of him.

1208
01:29:51,259 --> 01:29:53,117
I don't like it
when you do this!

1209
01:29:58,971 --> 01:30:01,621
Be nice, be nice!

1210
01:30:02,160 --> 01:30:03,551
I left everything...

1211
01:30:04,036 --> 01:30:05,978
I drove like a madman...

1212
01:30:06,098 --> 01:30:08,028
I killed two policemen...

1213
01:30:08,375 --> 01:30:09,945
Now I am here...

1214
01:30:10,065 --> 01:30:12,307
Be nice! Be nice!

1215
01:30:14,369 --> 01:30:15,652
Leave me alone!

1216
01:30:23,475 --> 01:30:24,111
No!

1217
01:30:25,214 --> 01:30:26,520
Calm down...

1218
01:30:27,156 --> 01:30:28,402
It's me...

1219
01:30:28,961 --> 01:30:30,172
Calm down!

1220
01:30:32,030 --> 01:30:33,433
It's me...

1221
01:30:36,914 --> 01:30:37,993
Come here...

1222
01:30:43,965 --> 01:30:44,913
It's ok!

1223
01:30:45,033 --> 01:30:45,836
Calm down...

1224
01:30:47,286 --> 01:30:48,497
It's me...

1225
01:30:50,022 --> 01:30:52,971
How many times
did we make love, Fabio?

1226
01:30:53,714 --> 01:30:55,632
One more time
won't change anything.

1227
01:30:55,752 --> 01:30:56,639
You know my body...

1228
01:30:56,759 --> 01:30:57,634
Quiet!

1229
01:30:58,773 --> 01:31:00,715
I don't love you!

1230
01:31:02,303 --> 01:31:04,773
What have you done to Alex
and my son?

1231
01:31:05,180 --> 01:31:07,410
Nothing happened,
I missed them.

1232
01:31:07,530 --> 01:31:09,387
What do you mean:
missed them?

1233
01:31:15,643 --> 01:31:17,166
Where is my son?

1234
01:31:18,316 --> 01:31:19,959
Don't do that!

1235
01:31:26,489 --> 01:31:30,337
It's not you I love!
Not you!

1236
01:31:30,757 --> 01:31:32,591
I don't love you!

1237
01:32:02,849 --> 01:32:04,252
Tell me we're close...

1238
01:32:04,671 --> 01:32:06,110
Almost there, kid.

1239
01:32:31,808 --> 01:32:33,055
Listen well...

1240
01:32:33,420 --> 01:32:36,357
Don't cry or get nervous,
do as I say...

1241
01:32:37,758 --> 01:32:39,448
I am counting on you.

1242
01:32:47,378 --> 01:32:48,265
Who is it?

1243
01:32:48,385 --> 01:32:49,344
Moineau.

1244
01:32:51,380 --> 01:32:52,604
What is going on?

1245
01:32:52,724 --> 01:32:54,533
Please keep hold of the kid
and call the police.

1246
01:32:54,653 --> 01:32:55,408
Why?

1247
01:32:55,528 --> 01:32:57,889
I can't explain but it's urgent.
Please!

1248
01:32:58,309 --> 01:33:01,556
Listen: stay right here,
do not go anywhere!

1249
01:33:41,087 --> 01:33:42,549
I am warning you...

1250
01:33:53,671 --> 01:33:55,577
Don't say anything
or I'll shoot.

1251
01:34:02,132 --> 01:34:03,175
Here I am.

1252
01:34:04,218 --> 01:34:06,256
Let go of him!

1253
01:34:07,418 --> 01:34:08,425
Watch out, Alex!

1254
01:34:14,739 --> 01:34:16,657
Get out of here!

1255
01:34:18,755 --> 01:34:20,589
Alex, run away,
get out!

1256
01:34:27,031 --> 01:34:28,314
Let me do it, Nicole...

1257
01:35:05,113 --> 01:35:06,792
You know him?

1258
01:35:07,691 --> 01:35:08,386
Yes.

1259
01:35:12,927 --> 01:35:14,078
Where is Marc?

1260
01:36:09,638 --> 01:36:10,849
It's over now.

1261
01:36:21,247 --> 01:36:22,745
It's nothing, kid.

1262
01:36:25,595 --> 01:36:27,345
I didn't want you to die.
